{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"StoreKitPlus builds on the great foundation that is provided by StoreKit 2 and just aims to make it easier to use StoreKit 2 in e.g. SwiftUI."}]},{"anchor":"Getting-products","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Getting products"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get products from StoreKit 2, you can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Product.products"},{"type":"text","text":" api:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let productIds = [\"com.your-app.productid\"]","let products = try await Product.products(for: productIds)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, if you need to fetch products in an abstract way, for instance if you need to mock this functionality in unit tests, inject additional functionality, etc., you can use the StoreKitPlus "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreService"},{"type":"text","text":", which has a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreService\/getProducts()"},{"type":"text","text":" function:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let productIds = [\"com.your-app.productid\"]","let products = try await service.getProducts()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StandardStoreService"},{"type":"text","text":" service implementation communicates directly with StoreKit and syncs the result to a provided, observable "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreContext"},{"type":"text","text":". Read more on this context further down."}]},{"anchor":"Purchasing-products","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Purchasing products"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To purchase products with StoreKit 2, you can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Product.purchase"},{"type":"text","text":" api:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let result = try await product.purchase()","switch result {","    case .success(let result): try await handleTransaction(result)","    case .pending: break","    case .userCancelled: break","    @unknown default: break","}","return result"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, if you need to purchase products in an abstract way, as described abovethe StoreKitPlus "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreService"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol has a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreService\/purchase(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":" function:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let result = try await service.purchase(product)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StandardStoreService"},{"type":"text","text":" service implementation communicates directly with StoreKit and syncs the result to a provided, observable "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreContext"},{"type":"text","text":". Read more on this context further down."}]},{"anchor":"Restoring-purchases","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Restoring purchases"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To restore purchase with StoreKit 2, you can use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Transaction.latest(for:)"},{"type":"text","text":" api and verify each transaction to see that it’s purchased, not expired and not revoked."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This involves a bunch of steps, which makes the operation pretty complicated. To simplify, you can use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreService\/restorePurchases()"},{"type":"text","text":" function:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["try await service.restorePurchases()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StandardStoreService"},{"type":"text","text":" service implementation communicates directly with StoreKit and syncs the result to a provided, observable "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreContext"},{"type":"text","text":". Read more on this context further down."}]},{"anchor":"Syncing-store-data","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Syncing store data"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To perform a full product information sync with StoreKit 2, you can fetch products and transactions from StoreKit."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This involves a bunch of steps, which makes the operation pretty complicated. To simplify, you can use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreService\/syncStoreData()"},{"type":"text","text":" function:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["try await service.syncStoreData()"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StandardStoreService"},{"type":"text","text":" service implementation communicates directly with StoreKit and syncs the result to a provided, observable "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreContext"},{"type":"text","text":". Read more on this context further down."}]},{"anchor":"Observable-state","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Observable state"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"StoreKitPlus has an observable "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StoreContext"},{"type":"text","text":" that can be used to observe the store state for a certain app."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let productIds = [\"com.your-app.productid\"]","let context = StoreContext()","let service = StandardStoreService(","    productIds: productIds,","    context: context",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The context lets you keep track of available and purchased products, and can be injected into a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/StandardStoreService"},{"type":"text","text":" to keep track of changes as the user uses the service to communicate with StoreKit."}]},{"anchor":"Local-products","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Local products"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to have a local representation of your StoreKit product collection, you can use the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/ProductRepresentable"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The protocol is just an easy way to provide identifiable product types, that can be matched with the real product IDs, for instance:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["enum MyProduct: CaseIterable, String, ProductRepresentable {","","    case premiumMonthly = \"com.myapp.products.premium.monthly\"","    case premiumYearly = \"com.myapp.products.premium.yearly\"","","    var id: String { rawValue }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can now use this collection to initialize a standard store service:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let products = MyProduct.allCases","let context = StoreContext()","let service = StandardStoreService(","    products: products,","    context: context",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also match any product collection with a context’s purchased product IDs:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let products = MyProduct.allCases","let context = StoreContext()","let purchased = products.purchased(in: context)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, some operations require that you provide a real StoreKit "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Product"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/storekitplus\/getting-started"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus\/Getting-Started","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"StoreKitPlus is a Swift-based library that adds extra functionality for working with StoreKit 2, like extensions, observable state, store services, etc."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Getting Started","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"StoreKitPlus"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/StoreKitPlus\/documentation\/StoreKitPlus"]]},"references":{"doc://StoreKitPlus/documentation/StoreKitPlus/StandardStoreService":{"role":"symbol","title":"StandardStoreService","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StandardStoreService"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This service class implements the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identi